ype\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring remote class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how remote classes utilize `java.lang.String[] main`. First, I need to load the class remotely by using methods like `findLoadedClass` and `findClass` to fetch it. After that, I’ll get its declared method and invoke it. This process seems intricate but understanding it step by step should help clarify how everything connects, especially with class loading and method invocation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class creation in javax package**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether we can create a class in the javax.* package within the test environment. However, JDK 9 and later versions prohibit defining classes in java.xml, which complicates things. Yet, I see that our test compile can create packages like javax.example. Still, there might be a conflict. I need to weigh these factors carefully to make an informed decision. Let's explore the implications further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AfXfW7dJo1spDGgUYntRfw7n|fc_0a9201999dd3f1db0169feefce9fe481a18df720f0b3968e29", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); mkdir -p \"$tmp/org_jboss_weld/weld_osgi_bundle\"; cat > \"$tmp/org_jboss_weld/weld_osgi_bundle/ViewerRemoteMain.java\" <<'EOF'\npackage org_jboss_weld.weld_osgi_bundle;\n\npublic final class ViewerRemoteMain {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        System.setProperty(\"javassist.viewer.remote.args\", String.join(\",\", args));\n    }\n}\nEOF\njavac --release 8 -d \"$tmp/classes\" \"$tmp/org_jboss_weld/weld_osgi_bundle/ViewerRemoteMain.java\"\nbase64 -w 100 \"$tmp/classes/org_jboss_weld/weld_osgi_bundle/ViewerRemoteMain.class\"\nrm -rf \"$tmp\"", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1426, "output": 2428, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28942, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}},