\n\nWhat it covers:\n\n- `Viewer.run(...)`\n- `ClassLoader#loadClass(String)` from `Viewer.run`\n- `Class#forName(String)` via `Viewer.class$`\n- `Class#getDeclaredMethod(...)`\n- `Method#invoke(...)`\n- `ClassLoader#findLoadedClass(...)`\n- `ClassLoader#findSystemClass(...)`\n\nThe test uses a `Viewer` subclass that supplies bytecode for a small target class, allowing `Viewer` to define and invoke the target `main` method on the JVM. It also handles Native Image unsupported dynamic class definition by verifying `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)` and rethrowing unexpected errors.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a9201999dd3f1db0169fef00f5b8081a18aa4c5657e6f35c2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 633, "output": 1027, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34428, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778315266405, "responseId": "resp_0a9201999dd3f1db0169fef003152881a1b85fc16d39e0e3d0"}}
